Bitcoin, ETH, LTC and so on are more on the speculation than investing side in my opinion. As Benjamin Graham says in "the Intelligent Investor":
- You must thoroughly analyze a company / an investment asset, and the soundness of it's underlying buisness or function before you buy in;
- You must delibarately protect yourself from serious losses;
- You must aspire to "adequate", not extraordinairy performance.
If you in relation to Cryptocurrencies feel like you have hit all of these benchmarks, then I say go for it.﻿
